    "title": "のは…だ: Identifying Who Did It",
    "explanation": "A new pattern: こわしたのはスニフだ — the one who broke it is Sniff. Here のは does not just nominalize an action — it identifies who performed it. [verb]た + のは + [person]だ.\n\n隠すのはよくない — hiding things is bad. 信じることができない — cannot believe. The familiar patterns continue alongside the new one.\n\nRe-read and find: when does のは identify a person vs. judge an action?"
